Source documents for bundling into ZIM files.

Organize by topic, then bundle:

  svalbard import --bundle radio-manuals sources/radio/*.pdf
  svalbard import --bundle medical-refs sources/medical/*

Structure:

  sources/
    radio/
      ham-radio-manual.pdf
      pmr-guide.pdf
    medical/
      first-aid.epub
      wilderness-medicine.pdf
    survival/
      army-survival-manual.pdf

After bundling, the ZIM appears in generated/ and is registered
as a local source. Attach it to a drive with:

  svalbard attach local:radio-manuals /path/to/drive
